## MSG91 Integration — What the Code Looks Like

### Send OTP (replace mock):
```ts
// ~15 lines of real code
const response = await fetch("https://control.msg91.com/api/v5/otp", {
  method: "POST",
  headers: {
    "authkey": process.env.MSG91_AUTH_KEY,
    "Content-Type": "application/json"
  },
  body: JSON.stringify({
    mobile: `91${mobile}`,
    template_id: process.env.MSG91_TEMPLATE_ID,
    otp_length: 6,
    otp_expiry: 5 // minutes
  })
})
```

### Verify OTP (replace mock):
```ts
// ~10 lines of real code
const response = await fetch(
  `https://control.msg91.com/api/v5/otp/verify?mobile=91${mobile}&otp=${otp}`,
  {
    headers: { "authkey": process.env.MSG91_AUTH_KEY }
  }
)
const data = await response.json()
if (data.type === "success") { /* OTP is valid */ }
```

That's literally it. The rest of your existing code (Medusa customer creation, JWT, cookie) stays exactly the same.

